In England, in the seven days to 25 September, there were 188,804 new confirmed cases (333.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 150,201 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 26% (38,603 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 30 September is 6,646,963 (11,754.1 cases per 100,000 population).
